</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="46D6F903276A3C31F043E68F2D5A9C05" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="22AAAA8CA7CC300EC7046D64524D2216" pageNumber="504">
diagnosis A medium-sized reddish yellow to brown member of the 
<taxonomicName id="BA7C3835911E3DD3251DEC80C909F4E1" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33744" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole flavens Roger" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole flavens Roger" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavens">flavens</taxonomicName>
group; both major and minor are immediately recognizable by the large, &quot;sharkfin&quot; shape of the humerus in dorsal-oblique view, meaning that the anterior margin is straight and the posterior margin convex in profile, tipped with an acute or right angle. Very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="38083745B087B06B31D07D8B8FDF2A6E" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181839" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole angulifera Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole angulifera Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulifera">angulifera</taxonomicName>
, and in varying degree also to 
<taxonomicName id="07C1DA5CAA3C06EC5B2E68AC95E5EB8A" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33595" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole arhuaca Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole arhuaca Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arhuaca">arhuaca</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="72113DBB1E10E259C295AAE564F2EAC9" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181854" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole caulicola Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole caulicola Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caulicola">caulicola</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="415897F261163A170A7809547D17D2A2" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33662" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole chalca Wheeler" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole chalca Wheeler" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalca">chalca</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2DB92FF0153DC7FE5E63B254CAA7BBB5" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181857" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole chalcoides Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole chalcoides Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalcoides">chalcoides</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="079B397B27F6DD0ACE4EAD86DFB5FC30" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181903" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole mincana Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole mincana Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mincana">mincana</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DA02F90500DA0FBD56259BB9DA26E160" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33982" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole sagana Wheeler" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole sagana Wheeler" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sagana">sagana</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7D9ACFEBE95475162AA687BC1F37245D" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181949" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tambopatae Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tambopatae Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tambopatae">tambopatae</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="55901216F65455362473C91155922AE0" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34062" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tragica Wheeler" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tragica Wheeler" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tragica">tragica</taxonomicName>
in overall appearance but distinctive in the humeral shape and other traits in body shape, sculpture, pilosity, and color.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2F2EC601FD028CA7626F398146E66538" type="description">
<paragraph id="7D38B0205B720B447C633E9A91F95A6D" pageNumber="504">Measurements (mm) Lectotype major: HW 0.94, HL 0.94, SL 0.46, EL 0.10, PW 0.48. Paralectotype minor: HW 0.50, HL 0.54, SL 0.58, EL 0.08, PW 0.34.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="680E4AB09E6521CADEDE680F564F3379" pageNumber="504">
color Lectotype major of 
<taxonomicName id="6B938AE44D038F07295EA3F84244D6AE" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181939" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole schmalzi Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole schmalzi Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schmalzi">schmalzi</taxonomicName>
: body and appendages light brown, waist and gaster dark brown (
<taxonomicName id="7BDB947E63A37DAFA7C149F8ACB6E440" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33961" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole rehi Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole rehi Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rehi">rehi</taxonomicName>
syntype major is yellowish brown; 
<taxonomicName id="E993BCC64690E3DD3FEF7E4FA32D24F0" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33960" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole rata Borgmeier" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole rata Borgmeier" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rata">rata</taxonomicName>
syntype major is light reddish yellow).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7F397DE635D5F5276CD3ADC015893BDC" pageNumber="504">
Paralectotype minors of 
<taxonomicName id="90103BAE8B0E986B1F94236C8830AC70" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181939" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole schmalzi Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole schmalzi Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schmalzi">schmalzi</taxonomicName>
: body light to medium brown, appendages light brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F1DCFAB84A3A122AA00EF984F5CC8585" pageNumber="504">
Syntype minors of synonymous 
<taxonomicName id="1A5E6AEFCE93549BC596E5E5C97B4297" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33961" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole rehi Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole rehi Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rehi">rehi</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D99BE6809C69A65520FCA39A1A93B428" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33960" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole rata Borgmeier" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole rata Borgmeier" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rata">rata</taxonomicName>
: light brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
